(Direct Speech Lesson) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Overview) Tj
T*
(Direct speech reports exact spoken words using quotation marks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Learning Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Explain the meaning of Direct Speech in English using accurate subject vocabulary.) Tj
T*
(- Describe the key ideas behind quotation punctuation and reporting exact words.) Tj
T*
(- Apply Direct Speech to examples such as writing a conversation using direct speech) Tj
T*
(correctly.) Tj
T*
(- Avoid common errors and build confidence through punctuating direct speech.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Main Lesson) Tj
T*
(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Direct speech reports exact spoken words using quotation marks. In a textbook lesson,) Tj
T*
(the first goal is to make the language idea clear. Students should be able to explain) Tj
T*
(what Direct Speech means, identify where it appears in English, and describe the main) Tj
T*
(purpose of the topic without relying on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Direct Speech is quotation punctuation and reporting exact words.) Tj
T*
(This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the idea actually) Tj
T*
(works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or patterns behind) Tj
T*
(Direct Speech and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In English, success) Tj
T*
(usually depends on understanding the meaning, form, and effect that belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Direct Speech is to connect the explanation directly to writing a) Tj
T*
(conversation using direct speech correctly. That kind of language example shows students) Tj
T*
(how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner should be able to) Tj
T*
(state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the question, and then apply) Tj
T*
(the interpretation or writing method with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. Why Errors Happen) Tj
T*
(One common difficulty in Direct Speech is forgetting punctuation or quotation marks.) Tj
T*
(This matters because many learners can repeat a definition but still fail to use it) Tj
T*
(correctly. A real textbook lesson should therefore point out not only the correct) Tj
T*
(method, but also the exact place where students often go wrong. Learning improves when) Tj
T*
ET
