(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect punctuating direct speech. The most effective habit is to read the) Tj
T*
(worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a similar) Tj
T*
(question alone. This turns Direct Speech into something the student can genuinely study) Tj
T*
(and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Direct Speech should first be understood as a language idea before it is treated as an) Tj
T*
(exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand quotation punctuation and reporting exact words because it) Tj
T*
(controls how questions in Direct Speech are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Direct Speech uses the correct interpretation or writing method and) Tj
T*
(explains why that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Writing a conversation using direct speech correctly is the type of application that) Tj
T*
(helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Direct Speech.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind quotation punctuation and) Tj
T*
(reporting exact words.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct interpretation or writing method step by step instead of jumping to) Tj
T*
(the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on writing a conversation using direct speech correctly.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in quotation punctuation and reporting exact words that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Direct Speech step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on punctuating direct speech.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid forgetting punctuation or quotation marks while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
